---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
  <Navbar />
  <main class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="effective-date"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> April 28, 2025</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>Welcome to Starmesh AI Inc. ("Company", "we", "our", or "us"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and personal information. This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our services - including our integrations with communication platforms, social media platforms, file storage providers, customer engagement tools, and other data sources.</p>
    <p>If you have questions or concerns, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@starmesh.ai">legal@starmesh.ai</a>.</p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We may collect the following categories of information, depending on the services and data sources you authorize:</p>
    <h3>a. Personal Information</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Name, email address, user ID, organization name, role/title</li>
      <li>Account information from connected platforms</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>b. Content and Communication Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Audio or video recordings (e.g., calls, meetings)</li>
      <li>Transcripts and notes</li>
      <li>Text-based content (e.g., social posts, emails, chats, comments)</li>
      <li>Document uploads or attachments</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>c. Metadata and System Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Meeting or message metadata (timestamps, participants, durations)</li>
      <li>Platform identifiers (e.g., meeting ID, user handles, file IDs)</li>
      <li>Usage metrics and feature interactions</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>d. Device and Access Data</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>IP address, browser type, OS, access timestamps</li>
      <li>Logs for authentication and request tracing</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We only collect data from third-party sources that you explicitly connect to and authorize.</p>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Provide and maintain our analytics and transformation services</li>
      <li>Extract insights, summaries, topics, and trends from unstructured data</li>
      <li>Help you track patterns, sentiment, performance, or user engagement</li>
      <li>Improve our algorithms, interfaces, and service experience</li>
      <li>Respond to inquiries and support requests</li>
      <li>Enforce security and legal compliance</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Data Sources and Integrations</h2>
    <p>Examples of integrations you may choose to connect with include (but are not limited to):</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Video conferencing (e.g., Zoom, Microsoft Teams, Google Meet)</li>
      <li>Messaging and collaboration tools (e.g., Slack, Intercom)</li>
      <li>Social media (e.g., Reddit, LinkedIn, X/Twitter)</li>
      <li>CRM and support platforms (e.g., Salesforce, Zendesk)</li>
      <li>Cloud storage (e.g., Google Drive, Dropbox)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Each data source has its own OAuth or credential-based access model. You may revoke access at any time.</p>

    <h2>5. Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information.<br />We may share your information only in these circumstances:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> Hosting, security, data processing providers (under confidentiality agreements)</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Obligations:</strong> If required by law or valid legal process</li>
      <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or asset sale (with notice)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We will never use your data to train external AI models, or disclose it for advertising purposes.</p>

    <h2>6. Security of Your Data</h2>
    <p>We use industry-standard measures to protect your information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Encryption (in transit and at rest)</li>
      <li>Role-based access controls</li>
      <li>Periodic security audits</li>
      <li>Data isolation between customers</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Despite our efforts, no system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure. We encourage you to use strong credentials and review authorized users regularly.</p>

    <h2>7. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
    <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Access or correct your personal data</li>
      <li>Request deletion or portability of your data</li>
      <li>Object to or restrict our use of your data</li>
      <li>Withdraw consent for optional processing</li>
    </ul>
    <p>To exercise these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:legal@starmesh.ai">legal@starmesh.ai</a>.</p>

    <h2>8. Data Retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>You have an active account</li>
      <li>It's needed for business or legal reasons</li>
      <li>It's needed to resolve disputes or enforce agreements</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Once no longer needed, we delete or anonymize the data securely.</p>

    <h2>9. International Transfers</h2>
    <p>Starmesh operates globally. If you are located outside the United States, your data may be transferred to — and processed in — the U.S. or other countries with adequate data protections in place.<br />We take reasonable steps to ensure your data is treated securely and lawfully.</p>

    <h2>10. Updates to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. If we make material changes, we will notify you by email or prominent notice on our website. The "Effective Date" at the top will always reflect the latest version.</p>

    <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>For questions or concerns:<br />
      Email: <a href="mailto:legal@starmesh.ai">legal@starmesh.ai</a><br />
      Website: <a href="https://www.starmesh.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://www.starmesh.ai</a>
    </p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
.legal-page {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 4rem auto 2rem auto;
  padding: 2.5rem 2.5rem 2rem 2.5rem;
  background: none;
  border-radius: 0;
  color: #F4F2FF;
  font-family: 'Lato', sans-serif;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.legal-page h1 {
  font-size: 2.4rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  color: #F4F2FF;
  font-weight: 800;
  text-align: left;
}
.effective-date {
  color: #E4D6F5;
  font-size: 1rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  text-align: left;
}
.legal-page h2 {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  color: #F4F2FF;
  font-weight: 700;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  text-align: left;
}
.legal-page h3 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  color: #F4F2FF;
  font-weight: 600;
  margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  margin-top: 2.2rem;
  text-align: left;
}
.legal-page p, .legal-page ul {
  font-size: 1.12rem;
  color: #E4D6F5;
  margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
}
.legal-page ul {
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
}
.legal-page li {
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
}
.legal-page a {
  color: #F4F2FF;
  text-decoration: underline;
}
.legal-page a:hover {
  color: #E4D6F5;
}
section {
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .legal-page {
    padding: 1.2rem 0.5rem;
  }
}
</style> 